<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="77" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="77">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName authority="Szépligeti, 1902" authorityName="Sharkey" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aerophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aerophilus fundacionbandorum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fundacionbandorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">Aerophilus fundacionbandorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honor of the BAND Foundation of the USA, in recognition of its decades of support for growth and development of Costa 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rica’s">Rica's</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Área">Area</normalizedToken>
de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Conservación">Conservacion</normalizedToken>
Guanacaste and most recently for adding 85 more hectares to ACG of original forest, Bosque 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Transición">Transicion</normalizedToken>
, lying on the nearly extinct fusion of dry forest with rain forest (http://www.gdfcf.org/content/
<normalizedToken originalValue="introducing-bosque-transición">introducing-bosque-transicion</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
